# Portable — local-first runtime (.env)
#
# TL;DR: in the happy path you need NO .env at all. Just run `portable start`.
#
# The backend runs on YOUR OWN PC (`portable start`), persists everything to local
# SQLite, and talks to AI/GitHub with YOUR OWN credentials. The launcher MINTS its
# own data-path JWT (auto-generates + persists a JWT_SECRET on first boot) and shows
# a pairing QR in the terminal.
#
# So NOTHING below is required to boot. On start the launcher AUTO-DISCOVERS the
# Anthropic + GitHub credentials already on your machine and uses them:
#   - Anthropic: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY / CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN env → local store →
#                ~/.claude/.credentials.json → macOS Keychain.
#   - GitHub:    GITHUB_TOKEN / GH_TOKEN env → local store → `gh auth token` →
#                ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml → the git credential helper.
# If you already have the `claude` CLI (or `gh`) set up, copy nothing — `portable
# start` runs with zero configuration. You only set a value below when one of the
# specific situations applies.
#
# Prerequisites are BINARIES, not env: Bun (https://bun.sh) and cloudflared
# (a missing cloudflared makes the launcher print install steps and stop).

# =================================
# AI credential — only if NOT auto-discovered
# =================================
# AI needs one Anthropic credential, but boot NEVER blocks on it (you just can't
# run AI until one is present). The launcher resolves it for you when possible:
#   - Preferred: a Claude *subscription* — if the `claude` CLI is installed and
#     missing a token, the launcher runs `claude setup-token` for you; the token
#     is kept in the local encrypted secret store, NOT here.
#   - Otherwise set a raw Anthropic API key here (uncomment + fill):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Calls always go direct to https://api.anthropic.com with your own credential.

# =================================
# GitHub access — only for the in-terminal login fallback
# =================================
# GitHub is OPTIONAL — you can connect it later from the Portable app. You only
# need this if GitHub wasn't auto-discovered AND you want to log in right in the
# terminal via the on-device OAuth device flow (scopes: repo read:org). It's the
# public OAuth-App client id; the token is stored locally, never on a server.
# GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=Iv1.xxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# =================================
# Optional: launcher identity / relay (defaults shown — override only if needed)
# =================================
# The launcher auto-generates + persists JWT_SECRET on first boot (local encrypted
# store). Set it ONLY to pin a specific secret (e.g. share one across reinstalls).
# JWT_SECRET=your_48_byte_hex_secret
# End-to-end encryption pre-shared key (base64, 32 bytes). Auto-generated +
# persisted on first boot and carried ONLY in the pairing QR (never over the
# network). Set it ONLY to pin a specific PSK (portable.dev#13).
# PORTABLE_E2E_PSK=base64_32_byte_key
# Hosted relay the launcher registers its rotating tunnel with. Override to point
# at a self-hosted gateway. Default: https://app.portable.dev
# PORTABLE_RELAY_URL=https://app.portable.dev
# Stable PC id (routing key, not a secret). Auto-generated + persisted if unset.
# PORTABLE_PC_ID=pc_xxxxxxxx
# Friendly PC label. Defaults to the hostname.
# PORTABLE_PC_LABEL=my-laptop
# Local API port (pinned to 127.0.0.1 by the launcher). Default: 4200.
# (Port 7878 is RESERVED by the dev system — do NOT use it here.)
# VGIT_PORT=4200
# Gateway base used for the outdated-client kill switch. Default: app.portable.dev
# GATEWAY_URL=https://app.portable.dev

# =================================
# Optional: paths (sensible defaults — override only if you want)
# =================================
# Where repos are cloned. Default: ~/claude-workspace
# WORKSPACE_DIR=~/claude-workspace
# Where local SQLite DBs + the encrypted secret store live. Default: ~/.portable
# DATA_DIR=~/.portable

# =================================
# Optional: Playwright Chromium path (browser automation uses local Playwright)
# =================================
# PLAYWRIGHT_CHROMIUM_EXECUTABLE_PATH="/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome"

# =================================
# Optional: Sentry (backend error logging — leave unset to disable)
# =================================
# SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0
# SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=local

# =================================
# Optional: misc tuning
# =================================
# Idle TTL (ms) before a live Claude session's subprocess is reaped; session_id
# is preserved so the next message resumes transparently. Default: 600000 (10m).
# CLAUDE_SESSION_IDLE_TTL_MS=600000
# Verbose logging.
# DEBUG=true
